## Summary

| Severity | Count | Pattern |
|---|---|---|
| 🔴 Critical | 6 | No assertions at all — method called, result discarded |
| 🟠 High | 4 | `Assert.IsNotNull` on non-nullable types — proves nothing |
| 🟡 Medium | 6+ | Missing negative/edge-case tests |

**Root cause:** Every test follows the same template — call the method, optionally `IsNotNull` the result, move on. This is the classic "coverage-touching" anti-pattern: the coverage tool sees every line executed, but zero behavioral contracts are verified. A mutation testing tool (e.g., Stryker.NET) would show near-0% mutation kill rate despite 95% line coverage.
